					<div style="background-image:url(http://www.gamnesia.com/images/avatars/uploads/avatar_8241.jpg)" class="news-header">
							<h2><a href="http://www.gamnesia.com/news/swery-wants-to-make-a-game-where-a-girl-masturbates-to-solve-crimes">Swery Wants to Make a Game Where a Girl Masturbates to Solve Crimes</a></h2>
							<h6>May 19 2015 by <a href="http://www.gamnesia.com/member/8241">Alex Hawkins</a></h6>
					</div>
					
					 
					<div class="content"><p>
   <img src="http://image-cdn.gamnesia.com/23472/whydontyourapforfood19__default-news-image.jpg" alt="" class="ci-image ci-default-news-image" style="float: left; margin: 0px 10px 10px 0px;">Game developer Swery is known for his offbeat, bizarre creations such as <em>Deadly Premonition</em> and <em>D4: Dark Dreams Don't Die</em>, but his latest idea may be the most strange of all of them so far. He remains busy trying to get <em>D4</em> over to PC and creating a possible return to <em>Deadly Premonition</em>, but during a <a href="http://metro.co.uk/2015/05/12/d4-on-pc-interview-swery-talks-pc-gaming-and-deadly-premonition-5192650/?hootPostID=1369d4801dc8106d0b6bdf9172155e58" target="_blank">recent interview with Metro</a> he revealed that he has another project on his mind. The project involves a young girl that uses masturbation to solve crimes:</p><blockquote>
   
<p>
   "Aside from that, I’m also working on a story about a high school girl detective who uses the imagination (fantasising) energy from masturbating to help her solve murders. But all the publishers keep telling me ‘There’s no way we could put out such a perverted game!’ LOL!" <strong>&mdash; Swery</strong>
   </p></blockquote><p>
   As Swery stated, no one is really up for helping in the creation of this game currently, so don't expect to be solving crimes using this unique power anytime soon.</p><p>
   What do you think about Swery's unusual concept? Let us know in the comments below!</p><p>
   <strong>Source:</strong> <a href="http://metro.co.uk/2015/05/12/d4-on-pc-interview-swery-talks-pc-gaming-and-deadly-premonition-5192650/?hootPostID=1369d4801dc8106d0b6bdf9172155e58" target="_blank">Metro</a></p></div>
					 
					 
					<div class="news-readmore well">
